properties.name: zoom
properties.description: Non-standard. Specifies the magnification scale of the object. See 'transform: scale()' for a standards-based alternative.

properties.name: -ms-ime-align
properties.description: Aligns the Input Method Editor (IME) candidate window box relative to the element on which the IME composition is active.

properties.name: -moz-binding
properties.description: The -moz-binding CSS property is used by Mozilla-based applications to attach an XBL binding to a DOM element.

properties.name: -moz-context-properties
properties.description: If you reference an SVG image in a webpage (such as with the element or as a background image), the SVG image can coordinate with the embedding element (its context) to have the image adopt property values set on the embedding element. To do this the embedding element needs to list the properties that are to be made available to the image by listing them as values of the -moz-context-properties property, and the image needs to opt in to using those properties by using values such as the context-fill value. This feature is available since Firefox 55, but is only currently supported with SVG images loaded via chrome:// or resource:// URLs. To experiment with the feature in SVG on the Web it is necessary to set the svg.context-properties.content.enabled pref to true.

properties.name: -moz-float-edge
properties.description: The non-standard -moz-float-edge CSS property specifies whether the height and width properties of the element include the margin, border, or padding thickness.

properties.name: -moz-force-broken-image-icon
properties.description: The -moz-force-broken-image-icon extended CSS property can be used to force the broken image icon to be shown even when a broken image has an alt attribute.

properties.name: -moz-image-region
properties.description: For certain XUL elements and pseudo-elements that use an image from the list-style-image property, this property specifies a region of the image that is used in place of the whole image. This allows elements to use different pieces of the same image to improve performance.

properties.name: -moz-orient
properties.description: The -moz-orient CSS property specifies the orientation of the element to which it's applied.

properties.name: -moz-outline-radius
properties.description: In Mozilla applications like Firefox, the -moz-outline-radius CSS property can be used to give an element's outline rounded corners.

properties.name: -moz-outline-radius-bottomleft
properties.description: In Mozilla applications, the -moz-outline-radius-bottomleft CSS property can be used to round the bottom-left corner of an element's outline.

properties.name: -moz-outline-radius-bottomright
properties.description: In Mozilla applications, the -moz-outline-radius-bottomright CSS property can be used to round the bottom-right corner of an element's outline.

properties.name: -moz-outline-radius-topleft
properties.description: In Mozilla applications, the -moz-outline-radius-topleft CSS property can be used to round the top-left corner of an element's outline.

properties.name: -moz-outline-radius-topright
properties.description: In Mozilla applications, the -moz-outline-radius-topright CSS property can be used to round the top-right corner of an element's outline.

properties.name: -moz-stack-sizing
properties.description: -moz-stack-sizing is an extended CSS property. Normally, a stack will change its size so that all of its child elements are completely visible. For example, moving a child of the stack far to the right will widen the stack so the child remains visible.

properties.name: -moz-text-blink
properties.description: The -moz-text-blink non-standard Mozilla CSS extension specifies the blink mode.

properties.name: -moz-user-input
properties.description: In Mozilla applications, -moz-user-input determines if an element will accept user input.

properties.name: -moz-user-modify
properties.description: The -moz-user-modify property has no effect. It was originally planned to determine whether or not the content of an element can be edited by a user.

properties.name: -moz-window-dragging
properties.description: The -moz-window-dragging CSS property specifies whether a window is draggable or not. It only works in Chrome code, and only on Mac OS X.

properties.name: -moz-window-shadow
properties.description: The -moz-window-shadow CSS property specifies whether a window will have a shadow. It only works on Mac OS X.

properties.name: -webkit-border-before
properties.description: The -webkit-border-before CSS property is a shorthand property for setting the individual logical block start border property values in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: -webkit-border-before-color
properties.description: The -webkit-border-before-color CSS property sets the color of the individual logical block start border in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: -webkit-border-before-style
properties.description: The -webkit-border-before-style CSS property sets the style of the individual logical block start border in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: -webkit-border-before-width
properties.description: The -webkit-border-before-width CSS property sets the width of the individual logical block start border in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: -webkit-line-clamp
properties.description: The -webkit-line-clamp CSS property allows limiting of the contents of a block container to the specified number of lines.

properties.name: -webkit-mask
properties.syntax: [ <mask-reference> || <position> [ / <bg-size> ]? || <repeat-style> || [ <box> | border | padding | content | text ] || [ <box> | border | padding | content ] ]#
properties.description: The mask CSS property alters the visibility of an element by either partially or fully hiding it. This is accomplished by either masking or clipping the image at specific points.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-attachment
properties.description: If a -webkit-mask-image is specified, -webkit-mask-attachment determines whether the mask image's position is fixed within the viewport, or scrolls along with its containing block.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-composite
properties.description: The -webkit-mask-composite property specifies the manner in which multiple mask images applied to the same element are composited with one another. Mask images are composited in the opposite order that they are declared with the -webkit-mask-image property.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-position
properties.description: The mask-position CSS property sets the initial position, relative to the mask position layer defined by mask-origin, for each defined mask image.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-position-x
properties.description: The -webkit-mask-position-x CSS property sets the initial horizontal position of a mask image.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-position-y
properties.description: The -webkit-mask-position-y CSS property sets the initial vertical position of a mask image.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-repeat-x
properties.description: The -webkit-mask-repeat-x property specifies whether and how a mask image is repeated (tiled) horizontally.

properties.name: -webkit-mask-repeat-y
properties.description: The -webkit-mask-repeat-y property specifies whether and how a mask image is repeated (tiled) vertically.

properties.name: accent-color
properties.description: Sets the color of the elements accent

properties.name: align-tracks
properties.description: The align-tracks CSS property sets the alignment in the masonry axis for grid containers that have masonry in their block axis.

properties.name: animation-composition
properties.description: The composite operation to use when multiple animations affect the same property.

properties.name: animation-range
properties.description: The animation-range CSS shorthand property is used to set the start and end of an animation's attachment range along its timeline, i.e. where along the timeline an animation will start and end.

properties.name: animation-range-end
properties.description: The animation-range-end CSS property is used to set the end of an animation's attachment range along its timeline, i.e. where along the timeline an animation will end.

properties.name: animation-range-start
properties.description: The animation-range-start CSS property is used to set the start of an animation's attachment range along its timeline, i.e. where along the timeline an animation will start.

properties.name: animation-timeline
properties.description: Specifies the names of one or more @scroll-timeline at-rules to describe the element's scroll animations.

properties.name: appearance
properties.description: Changes the appearance of buttons and other controls to resemble native controls.

properties.name: aspect-ratio
properties.description: The aspect-ratio   CSS property sets a preferred aspect ratio for the box, which will be used in the calculation of auto sizes and some other layout functions.

properties.name: azimuth
properties.syntax: <angle> | [ [ left-side | far-left | left | center-left | center | center-right | right | far-right | right-side ] || behind ] | leftwards | rightwards
properties.description: In combination with elevation, the azimuth CSS property enables different audio sources to be positioned spatially for aural presentation. This is important in that it provides a natural way to tell several voices apart, as each can be positioned to originate at a different location on the sound stage. Stereo output produce a lateral sound stage, while binaural headphones and multi-speaker setups allow for a fully three-dimensional stage.

properties.name: backdrop-filter
properties.description: The backdrop-filter CSS property lets you apply graphical effects such as blurring or color shifting to the area behind an element. Because it applies to everything behind the element, to see the effect you must make the element or its background at least partially transparent.

properties.name: border-block
properties.description: The border-block CSS property is a shorthand property for setting the individual logical block border property values in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: border-block-color
properties.description: The border-block-color CSS property defines the color of the logical block borders of an element, which maps to a physical border color depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-color and border-bottom-color, or border-right-color and border-left-color property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-block-style
properties.description: The border-block-style CSS property defines the style of the logical block borders of an element, which maps to a physical border style depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-style and border-bottom-style, or border-left-style and border-right-style properties depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-block-width
properties.description: The border-block-width CSS property defines the width of the logical block borders of an element, which maps to a physical border width depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-width and border-bottom-width, or border-left-width, and border-right-width property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-end-end-radius
properties.description: The border-end-end-radius CSS property defines a logical border radius on an element, which maps to a physical border radius that depends on on the element's writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-end-start-radius
properties.description: The border-end-start-radius CSS property defines a logical border radius on an element, which maps to a physical border radius depending on the element's writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-inline
properties.description: The border-inline CSS property is a shorthand property for setting the individual logical inline border property values in a single place in the style sheet.

properties.name: border-inline-color
properties.description: The border-inline-color CSS property defines the color of the logical inline borders of an element, which maps to a physical border color depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-color and border-bottom-color, or border-right-color and border-left-color property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-inline-style
properties.description: The border-inline-style CSS property defines the style of the logical inline borders of an element, which maps to a physical border style depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-style and border-bottom-style, or border-left-style and border-right-style properties depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-inline-width
properties.description: The border-inline-width CSS property defines the width of the logical inline borders of an element, which maps to a physical border width depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the border-top-width and border-bottom-width, or border-left-width, and border-right-width property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-start-end-radius
properties.description: The border-start-end-radius CSS property defines a logical border radius on an element, which maps to a physical border radius depending on the element's writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: border-start-start-radius
properties.description: The border-start-start-radius CSS property defines a logical border radius on an element, which maps to a physical border radius that depends on the element's writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: box-align
properties.description: The box-align CSS property specifies how an element aligns its contents across its layout in a perpendicular direction. The effect of the property is only visible if there is extra space in the box.

properties.name: box-direction
properties.description: The box-direction CSS property specifies whether a box lays out its contents normally (from the top or left edge), or in reverse (from the bottom or right edge).

properties.name: box-flex
properties.description: The -moz-box-flex and -webkit-box-flex CSS properties specify how a -moz-box or -webkit-box grows to fill the box that contains it, in the direction of the containing box's layout.

properties.name: box-flex-group
properties.description: The box-flex-group CSS property assigns the flexbox's child elements to a flex group.

properties.name: box-lines
properties.description: The box-lines CSS property determines whether the box may have a single or multiple lines (rows for horizontally oriented boxes, columns for vertically oriented boxes).

properties.name: box-ordinal-group
properties.description: The box-ordinal-group CSS property assigns the flexbox's child elements to an ordinal group.

properties.name: box-orient
properties.description: The box-orient CSS property specifies whether an element lays out its contents horizontally or vertically.

properties.name: box-pack
properties.description: The -moz-box-pack and -webkit-box-pack CSS properties specify how a -moz-box or -webkit-box packs its contents in the direction of its layout. The effect of this is only visible if there is extra space in the box.

properties.name: caret
properties.description: Shorthand for setting caret-color and caret-shape.

properties.name: caret-shape
properties.description: Specifies the desired shape of the text insertion caret.

properties.name: color-scheme
properties.description: The color-scheme CSS property allows an element to indicate which color schemes it can comfortably be rendered in.

properties.name: contain-intrinsic-size
properties.description: Size of an element when the element is subject to size containment.

properties.name: contain-intrinsic-block-size
properties.description: Block size of an element when the element is subject to size containment.

properties.name: contain-intrinsic-height
properties.description: Height of an element when the element is subject to size containment.

properties.name: contain-intrinsic-inline-size
properties.description: Inline size of an element when the element is subject to size containment.

properties.name: contain-intrinsic-width
properties.description: Width of an element when the element is subject to size containment.

properties.name: container
properties.description: The container shorthand CSS property establishes the element as a query container and specifies the name or name for the containment context used in a container query.

properties.name: container-name
properties.description: The container-name CSS property specifies a list of query container names used by the @container at-rule in a container query.

properties.name: container-type
properties.description: The container-type CSS property is used to define the type of containment used in a container query.

properties.name: content-visibility
properties.description: Controls whether or not an element renders its contents at all, along with forcing a strong set of containments, allowing user agents to potentially omit large swathes of layout and rendering work until it becomes needed.

properties.name: counter-set
properties.description: The counter-set CSS property sets a CSS counter to a given value. It manipulates the value of existing counters, and will only create new counters if there isn't already a counter of the given name on the element.

properties.name: font-optical-sizing
properties.description: The font-optical-sizing CSS property allows developers to control whether browsers render text with slightly differing visual representations to optimize viewing at different sizes, or not. This only works for fonts that have an optical size variation axis.

properties.name: font-palette
properties.description: The font-palette CSS property allows specifying one of the many palettes contained in a font that a user agent should use for the font. Users can also override the values in a palette or create a new palette by using the @font-palette-values at-rule.

properties.name: font-variation-settings
properties.description: The font-variation-settings CSS property provides low-level control over OpenType or TrueType font variations, by specifying the four letter axis names of the features you want to vary, along with their variation values.

properties.name: font-smooth
properties.description: The font-smooth CSS property controls the application of anti-aliasing when fonts are rendered.

properties.name: font-synthesis-position
properties.description: The font-synthesis-position CSS property lets you specify whether or not a browser may synthesize the subscript and superscript "position" typefaces when they are missing in a font family, while using font-variant-position to set the positions.

properties.name: font-synthesis-small-caps
properties.description: The font-synthesis-small-caps CSS property lets you specify whether or not the browser may synthesize small-caps typeface when it is missing in a font family. Small-caps glyphs typically use the form of uppercase letters but are reduced to the size of lowercase letters.

properties.name: font-synthesis-style
properties.description: The font-synthesis-style CSS property lets you specify whether or not the browser may synthesize the oblique typeface when it is missing in a font family.

properties.name: font-synthesis-weight
properties.description: The font-synthesis-weight CSS property lets you specify whether or not the browser may synthesize the bold typeface when it is missing in a font family.

properties.name: font-variant-emoji
properties.description: The font-variant-emoji CSS property specifies the default presentation style for displaying emojis.

properties.name: forced-color-adjust
properties.description: Allows authors to opt certain elements out of forced colors mode. This then restores the control of those values to CSS

properties.name: gap
properties.description: The gap CSS property is a shorthand property for row-gap and column-gap specifying the gutters between grid rows and columns.

properties.name: hanging-punctuation
properties.description: The hanging-punctuation CSS property specifies whether a punctuation mark should hang at the start or end of a line of text. Hanging punctuation may be placed outside the line box.

properties.name: hyphenate-character
properties.description: A hyphenate character used at the end of a line.

properties.name: hyphenate-limit-chars
properties.description: The hyphenate-limit-chars CSS property specifies the minimum word length to allow hyphenation of words as well as the minimum number of characters before and after the hyphen.

properties.name: image-resolution
properties.description: The image-resolution property specifies the intrinsic resolution of all raster images used in or on the element. It affects both content images (e.g. replaced elements and generated content) and decorative images (such as background-image). The intrinsic resolution of an image is used to determine the image’s intrinsic dimensions.

properties.name: initial-letter
properties.description: The initial-letter CSS property specifies styling for dropped, raised, and sunken initial letters.

properties.name: initial-letter-align
properties.description: The initial-letter-align CSS property specifies the alignment of initial letters within a paragraph.

properties.name: input-security
properties.description: Enables or disables the obscuring a sensitive test input.

properties.name: inset
properties.description: The inset CSS property defines the logical block and inline start and end offsets of an element, which map to physical offsets depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top and bottom, or right and left properties depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-block
properties.description: The inset-block CSS property defines the logical block start and end offsets of an element, which maps to physical offsets depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top and bottom, or right and left properties depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-block-end
properties.description: The inset-block-end CSS property defines the logical block end offset of an element, which maps to a physical offset depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top, right, bottom, or left property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-block-start
properties.description: The inset-block-start CSS property defines the logical block start offset of an element, which maps to a physical offset depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top, right, bottom, or left property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-inline
properties.description: The inset-inline CSS property defines the logical block start and end offsets of an element, which maps to physical offsets depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top and bottom, or right and left properties depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-inline-end
properties.description: The inset-inline-end CSS property defines the logical inline end inset of an element, which maps to a physical inset depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top, right, bottom, or left property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: inset-inline-start
properties.description: The inset-inline-start CSS property defines the logical inline start inset of an element, which maps to a physical offset depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation. It corresponds to the top, right, bottom, or left property depending on the values defined for writing-mode, direction, and text-orientation.

properties.name: justify-tracks
properties.description: The justify-tracks CSS property sets the alignment in the masonry axis for grid containers that have masonry in their inline axis

properties.name: line-clamp
properties.description: The line-clamp property allows limiting the contents of a block container to the specified number of lines; remaining content is fragmented away and neither rendered nor measured. Optionally, it also allows inserting content into the last line box to indicate the continuity of truncated/interrupted content.

properties.name: line-height-step
properties.description: The line-height-step CSS property defines the step units for line box heights. When the step unit is positive, line box heights are rounded up to the closest multiple of the unit. Negative values are invalid.

properties.name: margin-block
properties.description: The margin-block CSS property defines the logical block start and end margins of an element, which maps to physical margins depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation.

properties.name: margin-inline
properties.description: The margin-inline CSS property defines the logical inline start and end margins of an element, which maps to physical margins depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation.

properties.name: margin-trim
properties.description: The margin-trim property allows the container to trim the margins of its children where they adjoin the container’s edges.

properties.name: mask
properties.description: The mask CSS property alters the visibility of an element by either partially or fully hiding it. This is accomplished by either masking or clipping the image at specific points.

properties.name: mask-border
properties.description:
The mask-border CSS property lets you create a mask along the edge of an element's border.

This property is a shorthand for mask-border-source, mask-border-slice, mask-border-width, mask-border-outset, mask-border-repeat, and mask-border-mode. As with all shorthand properties, any omitted sub-values will be set to their initial value.

properties.name: mask-border-mode
properties.description: The mask-border-mode CSS property specifies the blending mode used in a mask border.

properties.name: mask-border-outset
properties.description: The mask-border-outset CSS property specifies the distance by which an element's mask border is set out from its border box.

properties.name: mask-border-repeat
properties.description: The mask-border-repeat CSS property defines how the edge regions of a source image are adjusted to fit the dimensions of an element's mask border.

properties.name: mask-border-slice
properties.description: The mask-border-slice CSS property divides the image specified by mask-border-source into regions. These regions are used to form the components of an element's mask border.

properties.name: mask-border-source
properties.description:
The mask-border-source CSS property specifies the source image used to create an element's mask border.

The mask-border-slice property is used to divide the source image into regions, which are then dynamically applied to the final mask border.

properties.name: mask-border-width
properties.description: The mask-border-width CSS property specifies the width of an element's mask border.

properties.name: mask-clip
properties.description: The mask-clip CSS property determines the area, which is affected by a mask. The painted content of an element must be restricted to this area.

properties.name: mask-composite
properties.description: The mask-composite CSS property represents a compositing operation used on the current mask layer with the mask layers below it.

properties.name: masonry-auto-flow
properties.description: The masonry-auto-flow CSS property modifies how items are placed when using masonry in CSS Grid Layout.

properties.name: math-depth
properties.description: Describe a notion of "depth" for each element of a mathematical formula, with respect to the top-level container of that formula.

properties.name: math-shift
properties.description: Used for positioning superscript during the layout of MathML scripted elements.

properties.name: math-style
properties.description: The math-style property indicates whether MathML equations should render with normal or compact height.

properties.name: max-lines
properties.description: The max-lines property forces a break after a set number of lines

properties.name: offset
properties.description: The offset CSS property is a shorthand property for animating an element along a defined path.

properties.name: offset-anchor
properties.description: Defines an anchor point of the box positioned along the path. The anchor point specifies the point of the box which is to be considered as the point that is moved along the path.

properties.name: offset-distance
properties.description: The offset-distance CSS property specifies a position along an offset-path.

properties.name: offset-path
properties.description:
The offset-path CSS property specifies the offset path where the element gets positioned. The exact element’s position on the offset path is determined by the offset-distance property. An offset path is either a specified path with one or multiple sub-paths or the geometry of a not-styled basic shape. Each shape or path must define an initial position for the computed value of "0" for offset-distance and an initial direction which specifies the rotation of the object to the initial position.

In this specification, a direction (or rotation) of 0 degrees is equivalent to the direction of the positive x-axis in the object’s local coordinate system. In other words, a rotation of 0 degree points to the right side of the UA if the object and its ancestors have no transformation applied.

properties.name: offset-position
properties.description: Specifies the initial position of the offset path. If position is specified with static, offset-position would be ignored.

properties.name: offset-rotate
properties.description: The offset-rotate CSS property defines the direction of the element while positioning along the offset path.

properties.name: overflow-anchor
properties.description: The overflow-anchor CSS property provides a way to opt out browser scroll anchoring behavior which adjusts scroll position to minimize content shifts.

properties.name: overflow-block
properties.description: The overflow-block CSS media feature can be used to test how the output device handles content that overflows the initial containing block along the block axis.

properties.name: overflow-clip-box
properties.description: The overflow-clip-box CSS property specifies relative to which box the clipping happens when there is an overflow. It is short hand for the overflow-clip-box-inline and overflow-clip-box-block properties.

properties.name: overflow-clip-margin
properties.description: The overflow-clip-margin CSS property determines how far outside its bounds an element with overflow: clip may be painted before being clipped.

properties.name: overflow-inline
properties.description: The overflow-inline CSS media feature can be used to test how the output device handles content that overflows the initial containing block along the inline axis.

properties.name: overlay
properties.description: The overlay CSS property specifies whether an element appearing in the top layer (for example, a shown popover or modal {{htmlelement("dialog")}} element) is actually rendered in the top layer. This property is only relevant within a list of transition-property values, and only if allow-discrete is set as the transition-behavior.

properties.name: overscroll-behavior
properties.description: The overscroll-behavior CSS property is shorthand for the overscroll-behavior-x and overscroll-behavior-y properties, which allow you to control the browser's scroll overflow behavior — what happens when the boundary of a scrolling area is reached.

properties.name: overscroll-behavior-block
properties.description: The overscroll-behavior-block CSS property sets the browser's behavior when the block direction boundary of a scrolling area is reached.

properties.name: overscroll-behavior-inline
properties.description: The overscroll-behavior-inline CSS property sets the browser's behavior when the inline direction boundary of a scrolling area is reached.

properties.name: overscroll-behavior-x
properties.description: The overscroll-behavior-x CSS property is allows you to control the browser's scroll overflow behavior — what happens when the boundary of a scrolling area is reached — in the x axis direction.

properties.name: overscroll-behavior-y
properties.description: The overscroll-behavior-y CSS property is allows you to control the browser's scroll overflow behavior — what happens when the boundary of a scrolling area is reached — in the y axis direction.

properties.name: padding-block
properties.description: The padding-block CSS property defines the logical block start and end padding of an element, which maps to physical padding properties depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation.

properties.name: padding-inline
properties.description: The padding-inline CSS property defines the logical inline start and end padding of an element, which maps to physical padding properties depending on the element's writing mode, directionality, and text orientation.

properties.name: page
properties.description: The page CSS property is used to specify the named page, a specific type of page defined by the @page at-rule.

properties.name: place-content
properties.description: The place-content CSS shorthand property sets both the align-content and justify-content properties.

properties.name: place-items
properties.description: The CSS place-items shorthand property sets both the align-items and justify-items properties. The first value is the align-items property value, the second the justify-items one. If the second value is not present, the first value is also used for it.

properties.name: place-self
properties.description: The place-self CSS property is a shorthand property sets both the align-self and justify-self properties. The first value is the align-self property value, the second the justify-self one. If the second value is not present, the first value is also used for it.

properties.name: print-color-adjust
properties.description: Defines what optimization the user agent is allowed to do when adjusting the appearance for an output device.

properties.name: rotate
properties.description: The rotate CSS property allows you to specify rotation transforms individually and independently of the transform property. This maps better to typical user interface usage, and saves having to remember the exact order of transform functions to specify in the transform value.

properties.name: row-gap
properties.description: The row-gap CSS property specifies the gutter between grid rows.

properties.name: ruby-merge
properties.description: This property controls how ruby annotation boxes should be rendered when there are more than one in a ruby container box: whether each pair should be kept separate, the annotations should be collapsed and rendered as a group, or the separation should be determined based on the space available.

properties.name: scale
properties.description: The scale CSS property allows you to specify scale transforms individually and independently of the transform property. This maps better to typical user interface usage, and saves having to remember the exact order of transform functions to specify in the transform value.

properties.name: scrollbar-color
properties.description: The scrollbar-color CSS property sets the color of the scrollbar track and thumb.

properties.name: scrollbar-gutter
properties.description: The scrollbar-gutter CSS property allows authors to reserve space for the scrollbar, preventing unwanted layout changes as the content grows while also avoiding unnecessary visuals when scrolling isn't needed.

properties.name: scrollbar-width
properties.description: The scrollbar-width property allows the author to set the maximum thickness of an element’s scrollbars when they are shown.

properties.name: scroll-margin
properties.description: The scroll-margin property is a shorthand property which sets all of the scroll-margin longhands, assigning values much like the margin property does for the margin-* longhands.

properties.name: scroll-margin-block
properties.description: The scroll-margin-block property is a shorthand property which sets the scroll-margin longhands in the block dimension.

properties.name: scroll-margin-block-start
properties.description: The scroll-margin-block-start property defines the margin of the scroll snap area at the start of the block dimension that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-block-end
properties.description: The scroll-margin-block-end property defines the margin of the scroll snap area at the end of the block dimension that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-bottom
properties.description: The scroll-margin-bottom property defines the bottom margin of the scroll snap area that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-inline
properties.description: The scroll-margin-inline property is a shorthand property which sets the scroll-margin longhands in the inline dimension.

properties.name: scroll-margin-inline-start
properties.description: The scroll-margin-inline-start property defines the margin of the scroll snap area at the start of the inline dimension that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-inline-end
properties.description: The scroll-margin-inline-end property defines the margin of the scroll snap area at the end of the inline dimension that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-left
properties.description: The scroll-margin-left property defines the left margin of the scroll snap area that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-right
properties.description: The scroll-margin-right property defines the right margin of the scroll snap area that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-margin-top
properties.description: The scroll-margin-top property defines the top margin of the scroll snap area that is used for snapping this box to the snapport. The scroll snap area is determined by taking the transformed border box, finding its rectangular bounding box (axis-aligned in the scroll container’s coordinate space), then adding the specified outsets.

properties.name: scroll-padding
properties.description: The scroll-padding property is a shorthand property which sets all of the scroll-padding longhands, assigning values much like the padding property does for the padding-* longhands.

properties.name: scroll-padding-block
properties.description: The scroll-padding-block property is a shorthand property which sets the scroll-padding longhands for the block dimension.

properties.name: scroll-padding-block-start
properties.description: The scroll-padding-block-start property defines offsets for the start edge in the block dimension of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-block-end
properties.description: The scroll-padding-block-end property defines offsets for the end edge in the block dimension of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-bottom
properties.description: The scroll-padding-bottom property defines offsets for the bottom of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-inline
properties.description: The scroll-padding-inline property is a shorthand property which sets the scroll-padding longhands for the inline dimension.

properties.name: scroll-padding-inline-start
properties.description: The scroll-padding-inline-start property defines offsets for the start edge in the inline dimension of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-inline-end
properties.description: The scroll-padding-inline-end property defines offsets for the end edge in the inline dimension of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-left
properties.description: The scroll-padding-left property defines offsets for the left of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-right
properties.description: The scroll-padding-right property defines offsets for the right of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-padding-top
properties.description: The scroll-padding-top property defines offsets for the top of the optimal viewing region of the scrollport: the region used as the target region for placing things in view of the user. This allows the author to exclude regions of the scrollport that are obscured by other content (such as fixed-positioned toolbars or sidebars) or simply to put more breathing room between a targeted element and the edges of the scrollport.

properties.name: scroll-snap-align
properties.description: The scroll-snap-align property specifies the box’s snap position as an alignment of its snap area (as the alignment subject) within its snap container’s snapport (as the alignment container). The two values specify the snapping alignment in the block axis and inline axis, respectively. If only one value is specified, the second value defaults to the same value.

properties.name: scroll-snap-stop
properties.description: The scroll-snap-stop CSS property defines whether the scroll container is allowed to "pass over" possible snap positions.

properties.name: scroll-snap-type-x
properties.description:
The scroll-snap-type-x CSS property defines how strictly snap points are enforced on the horizontal axis of the scroll container in case there is one.

Specifying any precise animations or physics used to enforce those snap points is not covered by this property but instead left up to the user agent.

properties.name: scroll-snap-type-y
properties.description:
The scroll-snap-type-y CSS property defines how strictly snap points are enforced on the vertical axis of the scroll container in case there is one.

Specifying any precise animations or physics used to enforce those snap points is not covered by this property but instead left up to the user agent.

properties.name: scroll-timeline
properties.description: Defines a name that can be used to identify the source element of a scroll timeline, along with the scrollbar axis that should provide the timeline.

properties.name: scroll-timeline-axis
properties.description: Specifies the scrollbar that will be used to provide the timeline for a scroll-timeline animation

properties.name: scroll-timeline-name
properties.description: Defines a name that can be used to identify an element as the source of a scroll-timeline.

properties.name: text-combine-upright
properties.description:
The text-combine-upright CSS property specifies the combination of multiple characters into the space of a single character. If the combined text is wider than 1em, the user agent must fit the contents within 1em. The resulting composition is treated as a single upright glyph for layout and decoration. This property only has an effect in vertical writing modes.

This is used to produce an effect that is known as tate-chū-yoko (縦中横) in Japanese, or as 直書橫向 in Chinese.

properties.name: text-decoration-skip
properties.syntax: none | [ objects || [ spaces | [ leading-spaces || trailing-spaces ] ] || edges || box-decoration ]
properties.description: The text-decoration-skip CSS property specifies what parts of the element’s content any text decoration affecting the element must skip over. It controls all text decoration lines drawn by the element and also any text decoration lines drawn by its ancestors.

properties.name: text-decoration-skip-ink
properties.description: The text-decoration-skip-ink CSS property specifies how overlines and underlines are drawn when they pass over glyph ascenders and descenders.

properties.name: text-decoration-thickness
properties.description: The text-decoration-thickness CSS property sets the thickness, or width, of the decoration line that is used on text in an element, such as a line-through, underline, or overline.

properties.name: text-emphasis
properties.description: The text-emphasis CSS property is a shorthand property for setting text-emphasis-style and text-emphasis-color in one declaration. This property will apply the specified emphasis mark to each character of the element's text, except separator characters, like spaces,  and control characters.

properties.name: text-emphasis-color
properties.description: The text-emphasis-color CSS property defines the color used to draw emphasis marks on text being rendered in the HTML document. This value can also be set and reset using the text-emphasis shorthand.

properties.name: text-emphasis-position
properties.description: The text-emphasis-position CSS property describes where emphasis marks are drawn at. The effect of emphasis marks on the line height is the same as for ruby text: if there isn't enough place, the line height is increased.

properties.name: text-emphasis-style
properties.syntax: none | [ [ filled | open ] || [ dot | circle | double-circle | triangle | sesame ] ] | <string>
properties.description: The text-emphasis-style CSS property defines the type of emphasis used. It can also be set, and reset, using the text-emphasis shorthand.

properties.name: text-size-adjust
properties.description: The text-size-adjust CSS property controls the text inflation algorithm used on some smartphones and tablets. Other browsers will ignore this property.

properties.name: text-underline-offset
properties.description: The text-underline-offset CSS property sets the offset distance of an underline text decoration line (applied using text-decoration) from its original position.

properties.name: text-wrap
properties.description: The text-wrap CSS property controls how text inside an element is wrapped.

properties.name: timeline-scope
properties.description: The timeline-scope CSS property modifies the scope of a named animation timeline.

properties.name: transform-box
properties.description: The transform-box CSS property defines the layout box to which the transform and transform-origin properties relate.

properties.name: transition-behavior
properties.description: The transition-behavior CSS property specifies whether transitions will be started for properties whose animation behavior is discrete.

properties.name: translate
properties.description: The translate CSS property allows you to specify translation transforms individually and independently of the transform property. This maps better to typical user interface usage, and saves having to remember the exact order of transform functions to specify in the transform value.

properties.name: view-timeline
properties.description: The view-timeline CSS shorthand property is used to define a named view progress timeline, which is progressed through based on the change in visibility of an element (known as the subject) inside a scrollable element (scroller). view-timeline is set on the subject.

properties.name: view-timeline-axis
properties.description: The view-timeline-axis CSS property is used to specify the scrollbar direction that will be used to provide the timeline for a named view progress timeline animation, which is progressed through based on the change in visibility of an element (known as the subject) inside a scrollable element (scroller). view-timeline-axis is set on the subject. See CSS scroll-driven animations for more details.

properties.name: view-timeline-inset
properties.description: The view-timeline-inset CSS property is used to specify one or two values representing an adjustment to the position of the scrollport (see Scroll container for more details) in which the subject element of a named view progress timeline animation is deemed to be visible. Put another way, this allows you to specify start and/or end inset (or outset) values that offset the position of the timeline.

properties.name: view-timeline-name
properties.description: The view-timeline-name CSS property is used to define the name of a named view progress timeline, which is progressed through based on the change in visibility of an element (known as the subject) inside a scrollable element (scroller). view-timeline is set on the subject.

properties.name: view-transition-name
properties.description: The view-transition-name CSS property provides the selected element with a distinct identifying name (a custom-ident) and causes it to participate in a separate view transition from the root view transition — or no view transition if the none value is specified.

properties.name: white-space
properties.syntax: normal | pre | nowrap | pre-wrap | pre-line | break-spaces | [ <'white-space-collapse'> || <'text-wrap'> || <'white-space-trim'> ]
properties.description: Specifies how whitespace is handled in an element.

properties.name: white-space-collapse
properties.syntax: collapse | discard | preserve | preserve-breaks | preserve-spaces | break-spaces
properties.description: The white-space-collapse CSS property controls how white space inside an element is collapsed.

properties.name: speak-as
properties.description: The speak-as descriptor specifies how a counter symbol constructed with a given @counter-style will be represented in the spoken form. For example, an author can specify a counter symbol to be either spoken as its numerical value or just represented with an audio cue.

properties.name: base-palette
properties.description: The base-palette CSS descriptor is used to specify the name or index of a pre-defined palette to be used for creating a new palette. If the specified base-palette does not exist, then the palette defined at index 0 will be used.

properties.name: override-colors
properties.description: The override-colors CSS descriptor is used to override colors in the chosen base-palette for a color font.

properties.name: ascent-override
properties.description: Describes the ascent metric of a font.

properties.name: descent-override
properties.description: Describes the descent metric of a font.

properties.name: font-display
properties.description: The font-display descriptor determines how a font face is displayed based on whether and when it is downloaded and ready to use.

properties.name: line-gap-override
properties.description: Describes the line-gap metric of a font.

properties.name: size-adjust
properties.description: A multiplier for glyph outlines and metrics of a font.

properties.name: bleed
properties.description: The bleed CSS at-rule descriptor, used with the @page at-rule, specifies the extent of the page bleed area outside the page box. This property only has effect if crop marks are enabled using the marks property.

properties.name: marks
properties.description: The marks CSS at-rule descriptor, used with the @page at-rule, adds crop and/or cross marks to the presentation of the document. Crop marks indicate where the page should be cut. Cross marks are used to align sheets.

properties.name: page-orientation
properties.description: The page-orientation CSS descriptor for the @page at-rule controls the rotation of a printed page. It handles the flow of content across pages when the orientation of a page is changed. This behavior differs from the size descriptor in that a user can define the direction in which to rotate the page.

properties.name: syntax
properties.description: Specifies the syntax of the custom property registration represented by the @property rule, controlling how the property’s value is parsed at computed value time.

properties.name: inherits
properties.description: Specifies the inherit flag of the custom property registration represented by the @property rule, controlling whether or not the property inherits by default.

properties.name: initial-value
properties.description: Specifies the initial value of the custom property registration represented by the @property rule, controlling the property’s initial value.

atDirectives.name: @font-face
atDirectives.description: 允许链接到在需要时自动激活的字体。这允许作者解决“网页安全”字体的限制，从而实现独立于给定用户环境中可用字体的一致呈现。

atDirectives.name: @font-feature-values
atDirectives.description: 为给定的字体系列定义用于选择备用字形的命名值。

atDirectives.name: @import
atDirectives.description: 包含另一个文件的内容。

atDirectives.name: @layer
atDirectives.description: 声明级联层和在多个级联层情况下的优先顺序。

atDirectives.name: @media
atDirectives.description: 为特定媒体类型定义样式表。

atDirectives.name: @-moz-document
atDirectives.description: Gecko-specific at-rule that restricts the style rules contained within it based on the URL of the document.

atDirectives.name: @-ms-viewport
atDirectives.description: 指定视口的大小、缩放因子和方向。

atDirectives.name: @namespace
atDirectives.description: 声明一个前缀，并将其与命名空间名称关联。

atDirectives.name: @-o-viewport
atDirectives.description: 指定视口的大小、缩放因子和方向。

atDirectives.name: @page
atDirectives.description: 指令定义各种页面参数。

atDirectives.name: @property
atDirectives.description: 描述自定义属性和变量的方面。

atDirectives.name: @supports
atDirectives.description: 条件组规则，其条件测试用户代理是否支持 CSS 属性：值对。

pseudoClasses.name: :active
pseudoClasses.description: Applies while an element is being activated by the user. For example, between the times the user presses the mouse button and releases it.

pseudoClasses.name: :any-link
pseudoClasses.description: Represents an element that acts as the source anchor of a hyperlink. Applies to both visited and unvisited links.

pseudoClasses.name: :checked
pseudoClasses.description: Radio and checkbox elements can be toggled by the user. Some menu items are 'checked' when the user selects them. When such elements are toggled 'on' the :checked pseudo-class applies.

pseudoClasses.name: :corner-present
pseudoClasses.description: Non-standard. Indicates whether or not a scrollbar corner is present.

pseudoClasses.name: :decrement
pseudoClasses.description: Non-standard. Applies to buttons and track pieces. Indicates whether or not the button or track piece will decrement the view's position when used.

pseudoClasses.name: :default
pseudoClasses.description: Applies to the one or more UI elements that are the default among a set of similar elements. Typically applies to context menu items, buttons, and select lists/menus.

pseudoClasses.name: :disabled
pseudoClasses.description: Represents user interface elements that are in a disabled state; such elements have a corresponding enabled state.

pseudoClasses.name: :double-button
pseudoClasses.description: Non-standard. Applies to buttons and track pieces. Applies when both buttons are displayed together at the same end of the scrollbar.

pseudoClasses.name: :empty
pseudoClasses.description: Represents an element that has no children at all.

pseudoClasses.name: :enabled
pseudoClasses.description: Represents user interface elements that are in an enabled state; such elements have a corresponding disabled state.

pseudoClasses.name: :end
pseudoClasses.description: Non-standard. Applies to buttons and track pieces. Indicates whether the object is placed after the thumb.

pseudoClasses.name: :first
pseudoClasses.description: When printing double-sided documents, the page boxes on left and right pages may be different. This can be expressed through CSS pseudo-classes defined in the  page context.

pseudoClasses.name: :first-child
pseudoClasses.description: 与:nth-child(1)相同。表示某个元素是其父元素的第一个子元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :first-of-type
pseudoClasses.description: 与:nth-of-type(1)相同。表示某个元素是其父元素的子元素列表中同类型的第一个兄弟元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :focus
pseudoClasses.description: 在元素具有焦点时应用（接受键盘或鼠标事件，或其他形式的输入）。

pseudoClasses.name: :fullscreen
pseudoClasses.description: 匹配任何设置了全屏标志的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :future
pseudoClasses.description: 表示任何在 :current 元素完全之后出现的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :horizontal
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于具有水平方向的任何滚动条部件。

pseudoClasses.name: :host
pseudoClasses.description: 在影子树的上下文中进行评估时，匹配影子树的宿主元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :host()
pseudoClasses.description: 当在影子树的上下文中评估时，如果主机元素在其正常上下文中匹配选择器参数，则匹配影子树的主机元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :host-context()
pseudoClasses.description: 测试是否存在一个在影子树之外的祖先元素，该元素匹配特定的选择器。

pseudoClasses.name: :hover
pseudoClasses.description: 应用于用户使用指向设备指定元素时，但不一定激活它时。例如，可视用户代理程序可以在鼠标悬停在元素生成的框上时应用此伪类。

pseudoClasses.name: :increment
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于按钮和跟踪片段。指示按钮或跟踪片段在使用时是否会增加视图的位置。

pseudoClasses.name: :indeterminate
pseudoClasses.description: 应用于值处于不确定状态的用户界面元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :in-range
pseudoClasses.description: 与范围输入、数字字段或其他接受这些属性的类型上的最小和最大属性一起使用。

pseudoClasses.name: :invalid
pseudoClasses.description: 当一个元素根据其他规范定义的数据有效性语义是有效的或无效的时，它分别为 :valid 或 :invalid。

pseudoClasses.name: :lang()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示处于指定语言中的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :last-child
pseudoClasses.description: 与:nth-last-child(1)相同。表示某个其他元素的最后一个子元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :last-of-type
pseudoClasses.description: 与:nth-last-of-type(1)相同。表示其父元素的子元素列表中同类型的最后一个兄弟元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :left
pseudoClasses.description: 在打印双面文档时，左右页面的页面框可能不同。 这可以通过 CSS 在页面上下文中定义的伪类来表示。

pseudoClasses.name: :link
pseudoClasses.description: 适用于尚未访问的链接。

pseudoClasses.name: :matches()
pseudoClasses.description: 将选择器列表作为其参数。 它表示由其参数表示的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-any()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示由其参数传递的选择器列表表示的元素。已标准化为 :matches()。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-any-link
pseudoClasses.description: 表示作为超链接的源锚点的元素。适用于已访问和未访问的链接。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-broken
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配表示损坏图像的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-drag-over
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。在拖动事件应用于其上时匹配元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-first-node
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。表示作为其他元素的第一个子节点的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-focusring
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配在浏览器中启用了焦点和焦点环绕绘制的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-full-screen
pseudoClasses.description: 匹配具有全屏标志设置的任何元素。标准化为 :fullscreen。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-last-node
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。表示作为其他元素的最后一个子节点的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-loading
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配尚未开始加载的元素，例如图像。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-only-whitespace
pseudoClasses.description: 与 :empty 相同，但它还额外匹配只包含受空白处理影响的代码点的元素。标准化为 :blank。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-placeholder
pseudoClasses.description: 已弃用。表示输入字段中的占位符文本。请在 Firefox 19+ 中使用 ::-moz-placeholder。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-submit-invalid
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。在关联表单的内容无效时，表示任何提交按钮。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-suppressed
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配被阻止加载的图像元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-ui-invalid
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。表示任何验证过的表单元素，其值无效。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-ui-valid
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。表示任何验证过的表单元素，其值有效。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-user-disabled
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配因用户偏好而被禁用的图像元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-moz-window-inactive
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。匹配非活动窗口中的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-ms-fullscreen
pseudoClasses.description: 匹配具有全屏标志设置的任何元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :-ms-input-placeholder
pseudoClasses.description: 表示输入字段中的占位文本。注意：对于 Edge，请使用伪元素 ::-ms-input-placeholder。标准化为 ::placeholder。

pseudoClasses.name: :-ms-keyboard-active
pseudoClasses.description: 仅适用于 Windows Store 应用。当元素聚焦并且用户按下空格键时，应用一个或多个样式。

pseudoClasses.name: :-ms-lang()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示处于指定语言的元素。接受逗号分隔的语言标记列表。

pseudoClasses.name: :no-button
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于跟踪片段。当该轨道末端没有按钮时应用。

pseudoClasses.name: :not()
pseudoClasses.description: 否定伪类，:not(X)，是一种功能性符号，它接受一个简单选择器（不包括否定伪类本身）作为参数。它表示一个不被其参数所表示的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :nth-child()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示在文档树中在它之前有an+b-1个兄弟元素，其中n是任何正整数或零值，并且有一个父元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :nth-last-child()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示在文档树中，某元素之后有 an+b-1 个同级兄弟元素，其中 n 为任意正整数或零，且该元素有父元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :nth-last-of-type()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示在文档树中，某元素之后有 an+b-1 个相同扩展元素名称的同级兄弟元素，其中 n 为任意零或正整数，且该元素有父元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :nth-of-type()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示文档树中在其之前有 an+b-1 个具有相同扩展元素名称的同级元素的元素，其中 n 为零或正整数值，并且具有父元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :only-child
pseudoClasses.description: 表示具有父元素并且其父元素没有其他子元素的元素。与 :first-child:last-child 或 :nth-child(1):nth-last-child(1) 相同，但具有较低的特异性。

pseudoClasses.name: :only-of-type
pseudoClasses.description: 匹配每个元素，该元素是其父元素下同类型元素中唯一的子元素。与:first-of-type:last-of-type或:nth-of-type(1):nth-last-of-type(1)相同，但具有较低的优先级。

pseudoClasses.name: :optional
pseudoClasses.description: 如果在所属表单提交之前对表单元素进行值的设置，则表单元素为 :required 或 :optional，分别表示该值为必填或可选。非表单元素既不是必填项也不是可选项。

pseudoClasses.name: :out-of-range
pseudoClasses.description: 与 min 和 max 属性一起使用，无论是在范围输入、数字字段或任何其他接受这些属性的类型上。

pseudoClasses.name: :past
pseudoClasses.description: 表示在 :current 元素之前完全定义发生的任何元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :read-only
pseudoClasses.description: 一个其内容不可更改的元素是 :read-only。然而，其内容可更改的元素（如文本输入框）被认为处于 :read-write 状态。在典型的文档中，大多数元素是 :read-only。

pseudoClasses.name: :read-write
pseudoClasses.description: 内容不可更改的元素是 :read-only。然而，内容可更改的元素（例如文本输入字段）被认为处于 :read-write 状态。在典型的文档中，大多数元素都是 :read-only。

pseudoClasses.name: :required
pseudoClasses.description: 如果一个表单元素在提交之前需要或者可选，则表单元素分别为 :required 或 :optional。不是表单元素的元素既不是必需的也不是可选的。

pseudoClasses.name: :right
pseudoClasses.description: 在打印双面文档时，左右页面的页面框可能不同。这可以通过 CSS 在页面上下文中定义的伪类来表示。

pseudoClasses.name: :root
pseudoClasses.description: 代表文档的根元素。在HTML 4中，这始终是HTML元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :scope
pseudoClasses.description: 代表处于上下文参考元素集中的任何元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :single-button
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于按钮和轨道部件。当两个按钮分别显示在滚动条的两端时应用。

pseudoClasses.name: :start
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于按钮和轨道元素。指示对象是否位于拇指之前。

pseudoClasses.name: :target
pseudoClasses.description: 一些URI指向资源内的位置。这种URI以一个'井号'（#）结尾，后面跟着一个锚标识符（称为片段标识符）。

pseudoClasses.name: :valid
pseudoClasses.description: 当元素根据其他规范中定义的数据有效性语义分别有效或无效时，元素为 :valid 或 :invalid。

pseudoClasses.name: :vertical
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。适用于具有垂直方向的任何滚动条部件。

pseudoClasses.name: :visited
pseudoClasses.description: 当链接被用户访问后应用。

pseudoClasses.name: :-webkit-any()
pseudoClasses.description: 表示由其参数传递的选择器列表表示的元素。标准化为 :matches()。

pseudoClasses.name: :-webkit-full-screen
pseudoClasses.description: 匹配任何设置了全屏标志的元素。标准化为 :fullscreen。

pseudoClasses.name: :window-inactive
pseudoClasses.description: 非标准。应用于所有滚动条部件。指示包含滚动条的窗口当前是否处于活动状态。

pseudoClasses.name: :current
pseudoClasses.description: :current CSS 伪类选择器是一个时间维度的伪类，表示当前正在显示的元素或元素的祖先。

pseudoClasses.name: :blank
pseudoClasses.description: :blank CSS 伪类选择空用户输入元素（例如 <input> 或 <textarea>）。

pseudoClasses.name: :defined
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :defined 表示已被定义的任何元素。这包括浏览器内置的任何标准元素，以及已成功定义的自定义元素（即使用 CustomElementRegistry.define() 方法定义的元素）。

pseudoClasses.name: :dir
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :dir() 根据其中包含的文本的方向性匹配元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :focus-visible
pseudoClasses.description: 当一个元素匹配 :focus 伪类并且用户代理通过启发式算法确定应该在元素上明显显示焦点时，:focus-visible 伪类生效。

pseudoClasses.name: :focus-within
pseudoClasses.description: 当一个元素匹配 :focus 伪类，并且该元素的后代在平面树中（包括非元素节点，如文本节点）满足匹配 :focus 的条件时，:focus-within 伪类生效。

pseudoClasses.name: :has
pseudoClasses.description: :has() CSS 伪类表示如果传递给参数的任何选择器（相对于给定元素的 :scope）至少匹配一个元素，则表示一个元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :is
pseudoClasses.description: :is() CSS 伪类函数接受选择器列表作为其参数，并选择该列表中任何一个选择器可以选择的元素。这对于以更紧凑的形式编写大型选择器非常有用。

pseudoClasses.name: :local-link
pseudoClasses.description: :local-link CSS 伪类表示指向同一文档的链接。

pseudoClasses.name: :paused
pseudoClasses.description: :paused CSS 伪类选择器是一个资源状态伪类，将匹配能够“播放”或“暂停”的音频、视频或类似资源，当该元素处于“暂停”状态时。

pseudoClasses.name: :placeholder-shown
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :placeholder-shown 表示当前显示占位符文本的任何 <input> 或 <textarea> 元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :playing
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :playing 是一个资源状态伪类选择器，将匹配能够“播放”或“暂停”的音频、视频或类似资源的元素，当该元素处于“播放”状态时。

pseudoClasses.name: :target-within
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :target-within 表示一个作为目标元素或包含作为目标的元素的元素。目标元素是一个具有与 URL 片段匹配的唯一 id 的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :user-invalid
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :user-invalid 表示任何已验证的表单元素，其值根据其验证约束无效，用户与之进行了交互后。

pseudoClasses.name: :user-valid
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类 :user-valid 表示任何已验证的表单元素，其值根据其验证约束正确验证。但与 :valid 不同的是，它仅在用户与之交互后匹配。

pseudoClasses.name: :where
pseudoClasses.description: 伪类函数 :where() 接受选择器列表作为其参数，并选择该列表中任何一个选择器可以选择的元素。

pseudoClasses.name: :picture-in-picture
pseudoClasses.description: :picture-in-picture CSS 伪类匹配当前处于画中画模式的元素。

pseudoElements.name: ::after
pseudoElements.description: 表示原始元素实际内容之后的可样式化子伪元素。

pseudoElements.name: ::backdrop
pseudoElements.description: 用于为位于顶层的元素（例如全屏显示的元素）创建遮罩，隐藏底层文档的背景。

pseudoElements.name: ::before
pseudoElements.description: 代表在原始元素实际内容之前的可样式化的子伪元素。

pseudoElements.name: ::content
pseudoElements.description: 已弃用。匹配分配列表本身，对具有分配列表的元素进行匹配。为了向前兼容，请使用::slotted。

pseudoElements.name: ::first-letter
pseudoElements.description: 代表元素的第一个字母，如果它在行上没有任何其他内容（例如图像或内联表格）作为前导。

pseudoElements.name: ::first-line
pseudoElements.description: 描述其源元素的第一行的内容。

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-list-bullet
pseudoElements.description: 用于样式化列表元素的项目符号。类似于标准化的 ::marker。

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-list-number
pseudoElements.description: 用于样式化列表元素的编号。类似于标准化的 ::marker。

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-placeholder
pseudoElements.description: 表示输入字段中的占位符文本。

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-progress-bar
pseudoElements.description: 代表进度条的条形部分。

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-selection
pseudoElements.description: 代表用户已经高亮显示的文档部分。

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-backdrop
pseudoElements.description: 用于创建一个背景，隐藏顶层元素（如全屏显示的元素）下面的文档。

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-browse
pseudoElements.description: 代表输入类型为文件的控件的浏览按钮。

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-check
pseudoElements.description: Represents the check of a checkbox or radio button input control.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-clear
pseudoElements.description: Represents the clear button of a text input control

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-expand
pseudoElements.description: Represents the drop-down button of a select control.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-fill
pseudoElements.description: Represents the bar portion of a progress bar.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-fill-lower
pseudoElements.description: Represents the portion of the slider track from its smallest value up to the value currently selected by the thumb. In a left-to-right layout, this is the portion of the slider track to the left of the thumb.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-fill-upper
pseudoElements.description: Represents the portion of the slider track from the value currently selected by the thumb up to the slider's largest value. In a left-to-right layout, this is the portion of the slider track to the right of the thumb.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-reveal
pseudoElements.description: Represents the password reveal button of an input type=password control.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-thumb
pseudoElements.description: Represents the portion of range input control (also known as a slider control) that the user drags.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-ticks-after
pseudoElements.description: Represents the tick marks of a slider that begin just after the thumb and continue up to the slider's largest value. In a left-to-right layout, these are the ticks to the right of the thumb.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-ticks-before
pseudoElements.description: Represents the tick marks of a slider that represent its smallest values up to the value currently selected by the thumb. In a left-to-right layout, these are the ticks to the left of the thumb.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-tooltip
pseudoElements.description: Represents the tooltip of a slider (input type=range).

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-track
pseudoElements.description: Represents the track of a slider.

pseudoElements.name: ::-ms-value
pseudoElements.description: Represents the content of a text or password input control, or a select control.

pseudoElements.name: ::selection
pseudoElements.description: Represents the portion of a document that has been highlighted by the user.

pseudoElements.name: ::shadow
pseudoElements.description: Matches the shadow root if an element has a shadow tree.

pseudoElements.name: ::target-text
pseudoElements.description: The ::target-text CSS pseudo-element represents the text that has been scrolled to if the browser supports scroll-to-text fragments. It allows authors to choose how to highlight that section of text.

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-range-progress
pseudoElements.description: The ::-moz-range-progress CSS pseudo-element is a Mozilla extension that represents the lower portion of the track (i.e., groove) in which the indicator slides in an <input> of type="range". This portion corresponds to values lower than the value currently selected by the thumb (i.e., virtual knob).

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-range-thumb
pseudoElements.description: The ::-moz-range-thumb CSS pseudo-element is a Mozilla extension that represents the thumb (i.e., virtual knob) of an <input> of type="range". The user can move the thumb along the input's track to alter its numerical value.

pseudoElements.name: ::-moz-range-track
pseudoElements.description: The ::-moz-range-track CSS pseudo-element is a Mozilla extension that represents the track (i.e., groove) in which the indicator slides in an <input> of type="range".

pseudoElements.name: ::-webkit-progress-inner-value
pseudoElements.description:
The ::-webkit-progress-value CSS pseudo-element represents the filled-in portion of the bar of a <progress> element. It is a child of the ::-webkit-progress-bar pseudo-element.

In order to let ::-webkit-progress-value take effect, -webkit-appearance needs to be set to none on the <progress> element.

pseudoElements.name: ::grammar-error
pseudoElements.description: The ::grammar-error CSS pseudo-element represents a text segment which the user agent has flagged as grammatically incorrect.

pseudoElements.name: ::marker
pseudoElements.description: The ::marker CSS pseudo-element selects the marker box of a list item, which typically contains a bullet or number. It works on any element or pseudo-element set to display: list-item, such as the <li> and <summary> elements.

pseudoElements.name: ::part
pseudoElements.description: The ::part CSS pseudo-element represents any element within a shadow tree that has a matching part attribute.

pseudoElements.name: ::placeholder
pseudoElements.description: The ::placeholder CSS pseudo-element represents the placeholder text of a form element.

pseudoElements.name: ::slotted
pseudoElements.description: The :slotted() CSS pseudo-element represents any element that has been placed into a slot inside an HTML template.

pseudoElements.name: ::spelling-error
pseudoElements.description: The ::spelling-error CSS pseudo-element represents a text segment which the user agent has flagged as incorrectly spelled.

pseudoElements.name: ::view-transition
pseudoElements.description: The ::view-transition CSS pseudo-element represents the root of the view transitions overlay, which contains all view transitions and sits over the top of all other page content.

pseudoElements.name: ::view-transition-group
pseudoElements.description: The ::view-transition-group CSS pseudo-element represents a single view transition group.

pseudoElements.name: ::view-transition-image-pair
pseudoElements.description: The ::view-transition-image-pair CSS pseudo-element represents a container for a view transition's "old" and "new" view states — before and after the transition.

pseudoElements.name: ::view-transition-new
pseudoElements.description: The ::view-transition-new CSS pseudo-element represents the "new" view state of a view transition — a live representation of the new view, after the transition.

pseudoElements.name: ::view-transition-old
pseudoElements.description: The ::view-transition-old CSS pseudo-element represents the "old" view state of a view transition — a static screenshot of the old view, before the transition.
